{"word":"θραύω","slug":"θραύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θραύω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to break in pieces, shatter, shiver</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to fly into pieces</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>frangere</el>, = <a href='S:θρύπτω'><el>θρύπτω</el></a>, <i>to break down, enfeeble</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}